  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen `truffle test` enumerates test files in `truffle-core/lib/commands/test.js`, it ignores errors returned by the `node-dir` callback. This in turn causes the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nTypeError: Cannot read property 'filter' of undefined\r\n    at truffle-core/lib/commands/test.js:47:1\r\n    at truffle-core/~/node-dir/lib/paths.js:72:1\r\n    at FSReqWrap.oncomplete (fs.js:166:21)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. `cd` to the root of any truffle project with tests\r\n2. Rename `test` to anything else (e.g. `tests-backup`)\r\n3. Run `truffle test`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nTruffle would exit with an error indicating that the `test` directory cannot be found (e.g. `ENOENT /path/to/project/test`).\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n```\r\nTypeError: Cannot read property 'filter' of undefined\r\n    at truffle-core/lib/commands/test.js:47:1\r\n    at truffle-core/~/node-dir/lib/paths.js:72:1\r\n    at FSReqWrap.oncomplete (fs.js:166:21)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: OS X\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 4.1.0, but from what I can tell, this impacts all truffle versions\r\n* node version (`node --version`): node version doesn't matter, but tested on v6.11.5, v9.3.0, and v9.7.1\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): Not important, but whatever `nvm` installs when it installs those versions of node.\r\n",
